article.headline: Columbia 75, Army 59
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. (AP) -- Gerard Barrett scored 13 points and grabbed nine rebounds to help Columbia beat Army 75-59 Tuesday night. Columbia (8-4) built on a 38-34 halftime lead by going on an 8-0 run to open the second half. Army (2-10) cut the deficit to 49-41 with 13:23 to go, but the Lions responded with a 16-5 spurt that put them up 65-46 midway through the half. Dragutin Kravic scored 12 points off the bench for Columbia, while Jeremiah Boswell had 11 and Tito Hill 10. Travis Owsley led Army with a season-high 13 points and four assists. Matt Bell added 10 points. Columbia shot 55.6 percent to Army's 42.9 percent.
